Document: NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData3D
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationmeshsourcegeometrydata3d.rst
Summary: This section details the methods available for manipulating and retrieving geometry data used in navigation mesh baking.

Method: add_faces(faces: PackedVector3Array, xform: Transform3D) → void
Adds an array of vertex positions to the geometry data for navigation mesh baking to form triangulated faces. Each face must have three vertex positions in clockwise winding order. The `xform` parameter is used to offset vertex positions by the node's transform.

Method: add_mesh(mesh: Mesh, xform: Transform3D) → void
Adds the geometry data of a Mesh resource to the navigation mesh baking data. The mesh must have valid triangulated mesh data. The `xform` parameter is used to offset vertex positions by the node's transform.

Method: add_mesh_array(mesh_array: Array, xform: Transform3D) → void
Adds an Array containing vertex and index data to the navigation mesh baking data. The array must have valid triangulated mesh data. The `xform` parameter is used to offset vertex positions by the node's transform.

Method: add_projected_obstruction(vertices: PackedVector3Array, elevation: float, height: float, carve: bool) → void
Adds a projected obstruction shape to the source geometry. The `vertices` define the shape on the XZ plane, `elevation` sets its Y position, `height` extrudes it, and `carve` determines if it's affected by navigation mesh baking offsets.

Method: append_arrays(vertices: PackedFloat32Array, indices: PackedInt32Array) → void
Appends `vertices` and `indices` arrays to the existing data, applying an offset to the appended indices.

Method: clear() → void
Clears all internal geometry data.

Method: clear_projected_obstructions() → void
Removes all previously added projected obstructions.

Method: get_bounds() → AABB
Returns an axis-aligned bounding box encompassing all stored geometry data. The bounds are cached and recalculated only when geometry data changes.

Method: get_indices() → PackedInt32Array
Returns the parsed source geometry data indices array.

Method: get_projected_obstructions() → Array
Returns the projected obstructions as an Array of Dictionaries. Each dictionary contains 'vertices', 'elevation', 'height', and 'carve' keys describing the obstruction.

Method: get_vertices() → PackedFloat32Array
Returns the parsed source geometry data vertices array.

Method: has_data() → bool
Returns true if there is any parsed source geometry data available.

Method: merge(other_geometry: NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData3D) → void
Adds the geometry data from another NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData3D instance to the current one.

Method: set_indices(indices: PackedInt32Array) → void
Sets the source geometry data indices. Warning: Incorrect data can cause baking process crashes.

Method: set_projected_obstructions(projected_obstructions: Array) → void
Sets the projected obstructions using an Array of Dictionaries. Each dictionary must contain 'vertices' (PackedFloat32Array), 'elevation' (float), 'height' (float), and 'carve' (bool).

Method: set_vertices(vertices: PackedFloat32Array) → void
Sets the source geometry data vertices. Warning: Incorrect data can cause baking process crashes.